; Per-tile top-row selector table (128 x 8 bytes), used by $8CF0
;
; .
;
; .
;
; One 8-byte row per tile ($8202, 0-127), spanning exactly #R$6C00-$6FFF
; (128*8=1024 bytes, ending precisely at #R$7000 where the sprite/mask data
; begins). Same selector-byte format as the paged-bank table at #R$C000
; (#R$8C00): bit0=variant, bits1-5=tile index (0-31), source
; addr=$E0+((byte>>1)&$1F):(bit0?$80:0), tiles at #R$E000-$FFFF. Read by
; #R$8CF0 to draw one extra background row directly onto the live screen
; (bypassing the shadow buffer, unlike #R$8C00's rows). Decode spot-checked
